==Cultural References and Origins==
It is widely accepted that '''meh''' was brought into the limelight by the television show ''[[w:The Simpsons|The Simpsons]]'', specifically in the episode titled ''"Hungry Hungry Homer"'' (Season 12, Episode 15,)

Homer: Kids... how would you... like to go to... Blocko Land??
Lisa/Bart: Meh.
Homer: But ... the TV gave me the impression that ...
Bart: We said "meh".
Lisa: M-e-h. Meh.

